38static u8
39nvkm_pm_count_perfdom(struct nvkm_pm *pm)
40{
41 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
42 u8 domain_nr = 0;
43
44 list_for_each_entry(dom, &pm->domains, head)
45 domain_nr++;
46 return domain_nr;
47}
48
49static u16
50nvkm_perfdom_count_perfsig(struct nvkm_perfdom *dom)
51{
52 u16 signal_nr = 0;
53 int i;
54
55 if (dom) {
56 for (i = 0; i < dom->signal_nr; i++) {
57 if (dom->signal[i].name)
58 signal_nr++;
59 }
60 }
61 return signal_nr;
62}
63
64static struct nvkm_perfdom *
65nvkm_perfdom_find(struct nvkm_pm *pm, int di)
66{
67 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
68 int tmp = 0;
69
70 list_for_each_entry(dom, &pm->domains, head) {
71 if (tmp++ == di)
72 return dom;
73 }
74 return NULL;
75}
76
77static struct nvkm_perfsig *
78nvkm_perfsig_find(struct nvkm_pm *pm, u8 di, u8 si, struct nvkm_perfdom **pdom)
79{
80 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = *pdom;
81
82 if (dom == NULL) {
83 dom = nvkm_perfdom_find(pm, di);
84 if (dom == NULL)
85 return NULL;
86 *pdom = dom;
87 }
88
89 if (!dom->signal[si].name)
90 return NULL;
91 return &dom->signal[si];
92}
93
94static u8
95nvkm_perfsig_count_perfsrc(struct nvkm_perfsig *sig)
96{
97 u8 source_nr = 0, i;
98
99 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sig->source); i++) {
100 if (sig->source[i])
101 source_nr++;
102 }
103 return source_nr;
104}
105
106static struct nvkm_perfsrc *
107nvkm_perfsrc_find(struct nvkm_pm *pm, struct nvkm_perfsig *sig, int si)
108{
109 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src;
110 bool found = false;
111 int tmp = 1; /* Sources ID start from 1 */
112 u8 i;
113
114 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(sig->source) && sig->source[i]; i++) {
115 if (sig->source[i] == si) {
116 found = true;
117 break;
118 }
119 }
120
121 if (found) {
122 list_for_each_entry(src, &pm->sources, head) {
123 if (tmp++ == si)
124 return src;
125 }
126 }
127
128 return NULL;
129}
130
131static int
132nvkm_perfsrc_enable(struct nvkm_pm *pm, struct nvkm_perfctr *ctr)
133{
134 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &pm->engine.subdev;
135 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
136 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = NULL;
137 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig;
138 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src;
139 u32 mask, value;
140 int i, j;
141
142 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
143 for (j = 0; j < 8 && ctr->source[i][j]; j++) {
144 sig = nvkm_perfsig_find(pm, ctr->domain,
145 ctr->signal[i], &dom);
146 if (!sig)
147 return -EINVAL;
148
149 src = nvkm_perfsrc_find(pm, sig, ctr->source[i][j]);
150 if (!src)
151 return -EINVAL;
152
153 /* set enable bit if needed */
154 mask = value = 0x00000000;
155 if (src->enable)
156 mask = value = 0x80000000;
157 mask |= (src->mask << src->shift);
158 value |= ((ctr->source[i][j] >> 32) << src->shift);
159
160 /* enable the source */
161 nvkm_mask(device, src->addr, mask, value);
162 nvkm_debug(subdev,
163 "enabled source %08x %08x %08x\n",
164 src->addr, mask, value);
165 }
166 }
167 return 0;
168}
169
170static int
171nvkm_perfsrc_disable(struct nvkm_pm *pm, struct nvkm_perfctr *ctr)
172{
173 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &pm->engine.subdev;
174 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
175 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = NULL;
176 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig;
177 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src;
178 u32 mask;
179 int i, j;
180
181 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
182 for (j = 0; j < 8 && ctr->source[i][j]; j++) {
183 sig = nvkm_perfsig_find(pm, ctr->domain,
184 ctr->signal[i], &dom);
185 if (!sig)
186 return -EINVAL;
187
188 src = nvkm_perfsrc_find(pm, sig, ctr->source[i][j]);
189 if (!src)
190 return -EINVAL;
191
192 /* unset enable bit if needed */
193 mask = 0x00000000;
194 if (src->enable)
195 mask = 0x80000000;
196 mask |= (src->mask << src->shift);
197
198 /* disable the source */
199 nvkm_mask(device, src->addr, mask, 0);
200 nvkm_debug(subdev, "disabled source %08x %08x\n",
201 src->addr, mask);
202 }
203 }
204 return 0;
205}

207/*******************************************************************************
208 * Perfdom object classes
209 ******************************************************************************/
210static int
211nvkm_perfdom_init(struct nvkm_perfdom *dom, void *data, u32 size)
212{
213 union {
214 struct nvif_perfdom_init none;
215 } *args = data;
216 struct nvkm_object *object = &dom->object;
217 struct nvkm_pm *pm = dom->perfmon->pm;
218 int ret, i;
219
220 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom init size %d\n", size);
221 if (nvif_unvers(args->none)) {
222 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom init\n");
223 } else
224 return ret;
225
226 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
227 if (dom->ctr[i]) {
228 dom->func->init(pm, dom, dom->ctr[i]);
229
230 /* enable sources */
231 nvkm_perfsrc_enable(pm, dom->ctr[i]);
232 }
233 }
234
235 /* start next batch of counters for sampling */
236 dom->func->next(pm, dom);
237 return 0;
238}
239
240static int
241nvkm_perfdom_sample(struct nvkm_perfdom *dom, void *data, u32 size)
242{
243 union {
244 struct nvif_perfdom_sample none;
245 } *args = data;
246 struct nvkm_object *object = &dom->object;
247 struct nvkm_pm *pm = dom->perfmon->pm;
248 int ret;
249
250 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom sample size %d\n", size);
251 if (nvif_unvers(args->none)) {
252 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom sample\n");
253 } else
254 return ret;
255 pm->sequence++;
256
257 /* sample previous batch of counters */
258 list_for_each_entry(dom, &pm->domains, head)
259 dom->func->next(pm, dom);
260
261 return 0;
262}
263
264static int
265nvkm_perfdom_read(struct nvkm_perfdom *dom, void *data, u32 size)
266{
267 union {
268 struct nvif_perfdom_read_v0 v0;
269 } *args = data;
270 struct nvkm_object *object = &dom->object;
271 struct nvkm_pm *pm = dom->perfmon->pm;
272 int ret, i;
273
274 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom read size %d\n", size);
275 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
276 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfdom read vers %d\n", args->v0.version);
277 } else
278 return ret;
279
280 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
281 if (dom->ctr[i])
282 dom->func->read(pm, dom, dom->ctr[i]);
283 }
284
285 if (!dom->clk)
286 return -EAGAIN;
287
288 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++)
289 if (dom->ctr[i])
290 args->v0.ctr[i] = dom->ctr[i]->ctr;
291 args->v0.clk = dom->clk;
292 return 0;
293}
294
295static int
296nvkm_perfdom_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
297{
298 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = nvkm_perfdom(object);
299 switch (mthd) {
300 case NVIF_PERFDOM_V0_INIT:
301 return nvkm_perfdom_init(dom, data, size);
302 case NVIF_PERFDOM_V0_SAMPLE:
303 return nvkm_perfdom_sample(dom, data, size);
304 case NVIF_PERFDOM_V0_READ:
305 return nvkm_perfdom_read(dom, data, size);
306 default:
307 break;
308 }
309 return -EINVAL;
310}
311
312static void *
313nvkm_perfdom_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
314{
315 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = nvkm_perfdom(object);
316 struct nvkm_pm *pm = dom->perfmon->pm;
317 int i;
318
319 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
320 struct nvkm_perfctr *ctr = dom->ctr[i];
321 if (ctr) {
322 nvkm_perfsrc_disable(pm, ctr);
323 if (ctr->head.next)
324 list_del(&ctr->head);
325 }
326 kfree(ctr);
327 }
328
329 return dom;
330}
331
332static int
333nvkm_perfctr_new(struct nvkm_perfdom *dom, int slot, u8 domain,
334 struct nvkm_perfsig *signal[4], u64 source[4][8],
335 u16 logic_op, struct nvkm_perfctr **pctr)
336{
337 struct nvkm_perfctr *ctr;
338 int i, j;
339
340 if (!dom)
341 return -EINVAL;
342
343 ctr = *pctr = kzalloc(sizeof(*ctr), GFP_KERNEL);
344 if (!ctr)
345 return -ENOMEM;
346
347 ctr->domain = domain;
348 ctr->logic_op = logic_op;
349 ctr->slot = slot;
350 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
351 if (signal[i]) {
352 ctr->signal[i] = signal[i] - dom->signal;
353 for (j = 0; j < 8; j++)
354 ctr->source[i][j] = source[i][j];
355 }
356 }
357 list_add_tail(&ctr->head, &dom->list);
358
359 return 0;
360}
361
362static const struct nvkm_object_func
363nvkm_perfdom = {
364 .dtor = nvkm_perfdom_dtor,
365 .mthd = nvkm_perfdom_mthd,
366};
367
368static int
369nvkm_perfdom_new_(struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon,
370 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
371 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
372{
373 union {
374 struct nvif_perfdom_v0 v0;
375 } *args = data;
376 struct nvkm_pm *pm = perfmon->pm;
377 struct nvkm_object *parent = oclass->parent;
378 struct nvkm_perfdom *sdom = NULL;
379 struct nvkm_perfctr *ctr[4] = {};
380 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
381 int c, s, m;
382 int ret;
383
384 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create perfdom size %d\n", size);
385 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
386 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create perfdom vers %d dom %d mode %02x\n",
387 args->v0.version, args->v0.domain, args->v0.mode);
388 } else
389 return ret;
390
391 for (c = 0; c < ARRAY_SIZE(args->v0.ctr); c++) {
392 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig[4] = {};
393 u64 src[4][8] = {};
394
395 for (s = 0; s < ARRAY_SIZE(args->v0.ctr[c].signal); s++) {
396 sig[s] = nvkm_perfsig_find(pm, args->v0.domain,
397 args->v0.ctr[c].signal[s],
398 &sdom);
399 if (args->v0.ctr[c].signal[s] && !sig[s])
400 return -EINVAL;
401
402 for (m = 0; m < 8; m++) {
403 src[s][m] = args->v0.ctr[c].source[s][m];
404 if (src[s][m] && !nvkm_perfsrc_find(pm, sig[s],
405 src[s][m]))
406 return -EINVAL;
407 }
408 }
409
410 ret = nvkm_perfctr_new(sdom, c, args->v0.domain, sig, src,
411 args->v0.ctr[c].logic_op, &ctr[c]);
412 if (ret)
413 return ret;
414 }
415
416 if (!sdom)
417 return -EINVAL;
418
419 if (!(dom = kzalloc(sizeof(*dom), GFP_KERNEL)))
420 return -ENOMEM;
421 nvkm_object_ctor(&nvkm_perfdom, oclass, &dom->object);
422 dom->perfmon = perfmon;
423 *pobject = &dom->object;
424
425 dom->func = sdom->func;
426 dom->addr = sdom->addr;
427 dom->mode = args->v0.mode;
428 for (c = 0; c < ARRAY_SIZE(ctr); c++)
429 dom->ctr[c] = ctr[c];
430 return 0;
431}

433/*******************************************************************************
434 * Perfmon object classes
435 ******************************************************************************/
436static int
437nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_domain(struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon,
438 void *data, u32 size)
439{
440 union {
441 struct nvif_perfmon_query_domain_v0 v0;
442 } *args = data;
443 struct nvkm_object *object = &perfmon->object;
444 struct nvkm_pm *pm = perfmon->pm;
445 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
446 u8 domain_nr;
447 int di, ret;
448
449 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfmon query domain size %d\n", size);
450 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
451 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfmon domain vers %d iter %02x\n",
452 args->v0.version, args->v0.iter);
453 di = (args->v0.iter & 0xff) - 1;
454 } else
455 return ret;
456
457 domain_nr = nvkm_pm_count_perfdom(pm);
458 if (di >= (int)domain_nr)
459 return -EINVAL;
460
461 if (di >= 0) {
462 dom = nvkm_perfdom_find(pm, di);
463 if (dom == NULL)
464 return -EINVAL;
465
466 args->v0.id = di;
467 args->v0.signal_nr = nvkm_perfdom_count_perfsig(dom);
468 strncpy(args->v0.name, dom->name, sizeof(args->v0.name));
469
470 /* Currently only global counters (PCOUNTER) are implemented
471 * but this will be different for local counters (MP). */
472 args->v0.counter_nr = 4;
473 }
474
475 if (++di < domain_nr) {
476 args->v0.iter = ++di;
477 return 0;
478 }
479
480 args->v0.iter = 0xff;
481 return 0;
482}
483
484static int
485nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_signal(struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon,
486 void *data, u32 size)
487{
488 union {
489 struct nvif_perfmon_query_signal_v0 v0;
490 } *args = data;
491 struct nvkm_object *object = &perfmon->object;
492 struct nvkm_pm *pm = perfmon->pm;
493 struct nvkm_device *device = pm->engine.subdev.device;
494 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
495 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig;
496 const bool all = nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvPmShowAll", false);
497 const bool raw = nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvPmUnnamed", all);
498 int ret, si;
499
500 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfmon query signal size %d\n", size);
501 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
502 nvif_ioctl(object,
503 "perfmon query signal vers %d dom %d iter %04x\n",
504 args->v0.version, args->v0.domain, args->v0.iter);
505 si = (args->v0.iter & 0xffff) - 1;
506 } else
507 return ret;
508
509 dom = nvkm_perfdom_find(pm, args->v0.domain);
510 if (dom == NULL || si >= (int)dom->signal_nr)
511 return -EINVAL;
512
513 if (si >= 0) {
514 sig = &dom->signal[si];
515 if (raw || !sig->name) {
516 snprintf(args->v0.name, sizeof(args->v0.name),
517 "/%s/%02x", dom->name, si);
518 } else {
519 strncpy(args->v0.name, sig->name,
520 sizeof(args->v0.name));
521 }
522
523 args->v0.signal = si;
524 args->v0.source_nr = nvkm_perfsig_count_perfsrc(sig);
525 }
526
527 while (++si < dom->signal_nr) {
528 if (all || dom->signal[si].name) {
529 args->v0.iter = ++si;
530 return 0;
531 }
532 }
533
534 args->v0.iter = 0xffff;
535 return 0;
536}
537
538static int
539nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_source(struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon,
540 void *data, u32 size)
541{
542 union {
543 struct nvif_perfmon_query_source_v0 v0;
544 } *args = data;
545 struct nvkm_object *object = &perfmon->object;
546 struct nvkm_pm *pm = perfmon->pm;
547 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom = NULL;
548 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig;
549 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src;
550 u8 source_nr = 0;
551 int si, ret;
552
553 nvif_ioctl(object, "perfmon query source size %d\n", size);
554 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
555 nvif_ioctl(object,
556 "perfmon source vers %d dom %d sig %02x iter %02x\n",
557 args->v0.version, args->v0.domain, args->v0.signal,
558 args->v0.iter);
559 si = (args->v0.iter & 0xff) - 1;
560 } else
561 return ret;
562
563 sig = nvkm_perfsig_find(pm, args->v0.domain, args->v0.signal, &dom);
564 if (!sig)
565 return -EINVAL;
566
567 source_nr = nvkm_perfsig_count_perfsrc(sig);
568 if (si >= (int)source_nr)
569 return -EINVAL;
570
571 if (si >= 0) {
572 src = nvkm_perfsrc_find(pm, sig, sig->source[si]);
573 if (!src)
574 return -EINVAL;
575
576 args->v0.source = sig->source[si];
577 args->v0.mask = src->mask;
578 strncpy(args->v0.name, src->name, sizeof(args->v0.name));
579 }
580
581 if (++si < source_nr) {
582 args->v0.iter = ++si;
583 return 0;
584 }
585
586 args->v0.iter = 0xff;
587 return 0;
588}
589
590static int
591nvkm_perfmon_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
592{
593 struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon = nvkm_perfmon(object);
594 switch (mthd) {
595 case NVIF_PERFMON_V0_QUERY_DOMAIN:
596 return nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_domain(perfmon, data, size);
597 case NVIF_PERFMON_V0_QUERY_SIGNAL:
598 return nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_signal(perfmon, data, size);
599 case NVIF_PERFMON_V0_QUERY_SOURCE:
600 return nvkm_perfmon_mthd_query_source(perfmon, data, size);
601 default:
602 break;
603 }
604 return -EINVAL;
605}
606
607static int
608nvkm_perfmon_child_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
609 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
610{
611 struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon = nvkm_perfmon(oclass->parent);
612 return nvkm_perfdom_new_(perfmon, oclass, data, size, pobject);
613}
614
615static int
616nvkm_perfmon_child_get(struct nvkm_object *object, int index,
617 struct nvkm_oclass *oclass)
618{
619 if (index == 0) {
620 oclass->base.oclass = NVIF_IOCTL_NEW_V0_PERFDOM;
621 oclass->base.minver = 0;
622 oclass->base.maxver = 0;
623 oclass->ctor = nvkm_perfmon_child_new;
624 return 0;
625 }
626 return -EINVAL;
627}
628
629static void *
630nvkm_perfmon_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
631{
632 struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon = nvkm_perfmon(object);
633 struct nvkm_pm *pm = perfmon->pm;
634 mutex_lock(&pm->engine.subdev.mutex);
635 if (pm->perfmon == &perfmon->object)
636 pm->perfmon = NULL;
637 mutex_unlock(&pm->engine.subdev.mutex);
638 return perfmon;
639}
640
641static const struct nvkm_object_func
642nvkm_perfmon = {
643 .dtor = nvkm_perfmon_dtor,
644 .mthd = nvkm_perfmon_mthd,
645 .sclass = nvkm_perfmon_child_get,
646};
647
648static int
649nvkm_perfmon_new(struct nvkm_pm *pm, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
650 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
651{
652 struct nvkm_perfmon *perfmon;
653
654 if (!(perfmon = kzalloc(sizeof(*perfmon), GFP_KERNEL)))
655 return -ENOMEM;
656 nvkm_object_ctor(&nvkm_perfmon, oclass, &perfmon->object);
657 perfmon->pm = pm;
658 *pobject = &perfmon->object;
659 return 0;
660}
661
662/*******************************************************************************
663 * PPM engine/subdev functions
664 ******************************************************************************/
665
666static int
667nvkm_pm_oclass_new(struct nvkm_device *device, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
668 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
669{
670 struct nvkm_pm *pm = nvkm_pm(oclass->engine);
671 int ret;
672
673 ret = nvkm_perfmon_new(pm, oclass, data, size, pobject);
674 if (ret)
675 return ret;
676
677 mutex_lock(&pm->engine.subdev.mutex);
678 if (pm->perfmon == NULL)
679 pm->perfmon = *pobject;
680 ret = (pm->perfmon == *pobject) ? 0 : -EBUSY;
681 mutex_unlock(&pm->engine.subdev.mutex);
682 return ret;
683}
684
685static const struct nvkm_device_oclass
686nvkm_pm_oclass = {
687 .base.oclass = NVIF_IOCTL_NEW_V0_PERFMON,
688 .base.minver = -1,
689 .base.maxver = -1,
690 .ctor = nvkm_pm_oclass_new,
691};
692
693static int
694nvkm_pm_oclass_get(struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, int index,
695 const struct nvkm_device_oclass **class)
696{
697 if (index == 0) {
698 oclass->base = nvkm_pm_oclass.base;
699 *class = &nvkm_pm_oclass;
700 return index;
701 }
702 return 1;
703}
704
705static int
706nvkm_perfsrc_new(struct nvkm_pm *pm, struct nvkm_perfsig *sig,
707 const struct nvkm_specsrc *spec)
708{
709 const struct nvkm_specsrc *ssrc;
710 const struct nvkm_specmux *smux;
711 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src;
712 u8 source_nr = 0;
713
714 if (!spec) {
715 /* No sources are defined for this signal. */
716 return 0;
717 }
718
719 ssrc = spec;
720 while (ssrc->name) {
721 smux = ssrc->mux;
722 while (smux->name) {
723 bool found = false;
724 u8 source_id = 0;
725 u32 len;
726
727 list_for_each_entry(src, &pm->sources, head) {
728 if (src->addr == ssrc->addr &&
729 src->shift == smux->shift) {
730 found = true;
731 break;
732 }
733 source_id++;
734 }
735
736 if (!found) {
737 src = kzalloc(sizeof(*src), GFP_KERNEL);
738 if (!src)
739 return -ENOMEM;
740
741 src->addr = ssrc->addr;
742 src->mask = smux->mask;
743 src->shift = smux->shift;
744 src->enable = smux->enable;
745
746 len = strlen(ssrc->name) +
747 strlen(smux->name) + 2;
748 src->name = kzalloc(len, GFP_KERNEL);
749 if (!src->name) {
750 kfree(src);
751 return -ENOMEM;
752 }
753 snprintf(src->name, len, "%s_%s", ssrc->name,
754 smux->name);
755
756 list_add_tail(&src->head, &pm->sources);
757 }
758
759 sig->source[source_nr++] = source_id + 1;
760 smux++;
761 }
762 ssrc++;
763 }
764
765 return 0;
766}
767
768int
769nvkm_perfdom_new(struct nvkm_pm *pm, const char *name, u32 mask,
770 u32 base, u32 size_unit, u32 size_domain,
771 const struct nvkm_specdom *spec)
772{
773 const struct nvkm_specdom *sdom;
774 const struct nvkm_specsig *ssig;
775 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom;
776 int ret, i;
777
778 for (i = 0; i == 0 || mask; i++) {
779 u32 addr = base + (i * size_unit);
780 if (i && !(mask & (1 << i)))
781 continue;
782
783 sdom = spec;
784 while (sdom->signal_nr) {
785 dom = kzalloc(sizeof(*dom) + sdom->signal_nr *
786 sizeof(*dom->signal), GFP_KERNEL);
787 if (!dom)
788 return -ENOMEM;
789
790 if (mask) {
791 snprintf(dom->name, sizeof(dom->name),
792 "%s/%02x/%02x", name, i,
793 (int)(sdom - spec));
794 } else {
795 snprintf(dom->name, sizeof(dom->name),
796 "%s/%02x", name, (int)(sdom - spec));
797 }
798
799 list_add_tail(&dom->head, &pm->domains);
800 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dom->list);
801 dom->func = sdom->func;
802 dom->addr = addr;
803 dom->signal_nr = sdom->signal_nr;
804
805 ssig = (sdom++)->signal;
806 while (ssig->name) {
807 struct nvkm_perfsig *sig =
808 &dom->signal[ssig->signal];
809 sig->name = ssig->name;
810 ret = nvkm_perfsrc_new(pm, sig, ssig->source);
811 if (ret)
812 return ret;
813 ssig++;
814 }
815
816 addr += size_domain;
817 }
818
819 mask &= ~(1 << i);
820 }
821
822 return 0;
823}
824
825static int
826nvkm_pm_fini(struct nvkm_engine *engine, bool suspend)
827{
828 struct nvkm_pm *pm = nvkm_pm(engine);
829 if (pm->func->fini)
830 pm->func->fini(pm);
831 return 0;
832}
833
834static void *
835nvkm_pm_dtor(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
836{
837 struct nvkm_pm *pm = nvkm_pm(engine);
838 struct nvkm_perfdom *dom, *next_dom;
839 struct nvkm_perfsrc *src, *next_src;
840
841 list_for_each_entry_safe(dom, next_dom, &pm->domains, head) {
842 list_del(&dom->head);
843 kfree(dom);
844 }
845
846 list_for_each_entry_safe(src, next_src, &pm->sources, head) {
847 list_del(&src->head);
848 kfree(src->name);
849 kfree(src);
850 }
851
852 return pm;
853}
854
855static const struct nvkm_engine_func
856nvkm_pm = {
857 .dtor = nvkm_pm_dtor,
858 .fini = nvkm_pm_fini,
859 .base.sclass = nvkm_pm_oclass_get,
860};
861
862int
863nvkm_pm_ctor(const struct nvkm_pm_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
864 int index, struct nvkm_pm *pm)
865{
866 pm->func = func;
867 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pm->domains);
868 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pm->sources);
869 return nvkm_engine_ctor(&nvkm_pm, device, index, 0, true, &pm->engine);
870}
